The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at a National Military Appreciation Month event at the White House. Pence thanked veterans for their service and highlighted the importance of honoring and supporting them. He also discussed President Trump's commitment to improving the Department of Veterans Affairs and increasing defense spending. Pence shared personal stories about his father's military service and his own pride in having a son in the Marines. He concluded by expressing gratitude to all veterans and pledging continued support for the military.